        a                        fabio:Figure ;
        dc:description           "FIGURE 3 European lower Aptian shorelines. Stipple indicates land areas. 1: area from which the corals of the Swiss localities were derived (paleocoordinates of Hergiswil: 32° 24’ N, 18° 48’ E). 2: area from which the corals of the Austrian and German localities were derived (paleocoordinates of the area Allgäu Schrattenkalk/Brandalpe-Kuhberg: 31° 54’ N, 20° 18’ E) (map modified from TYSON & FUNNELL, 1987; paleocoordinates from Paleobiology Database [paleobiodb.org)." ;
        fabio:hasRepresentation  "https://zenodo.org/record/4693805/files/figure.png" .

